  "text": "If our attention is turned to national political leaders rather than to states, then it becomes apparent that fundamental policy choices -even war and peace choices -may be made without regard for citizen welfare or the national interest. One has only to reflect on Myanmar's ruling junta, North Korea's Kim Jong-il, or Zaire's late Mobutu Sese-Seko to recognize that many leaders govern for their own benefit at the cost of the welfare of their subjects. So many nations have been beggared by their leaders that it is difficult to see how we can maintain the fiction that the national interest dictates even the most important foreign policy choices. James [CITATION_1] ",
